      <hedline>
        <hl1>Carry-On Bags</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Barbara Barron on Betsy Wade's Dec 21, 1997 Practical Traveler column on crackdown by airline carriers on carry-on luggage (S)1</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: The luggage bins' latches are very weak. What they need are bracelet-type double locks, one that overlaps the under latch.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: The luggage bins' latches are very weak. What they need are bracelet-type double locks, one that overlaps the under latch.</p>
        <p>It's not what is put into the bins, if it fits properly; it's how the items are prevented from falling out onto an innocent passenger.</p>
        <p>BARBARA BARRON  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
